thin thought itself. Thought Under Threat alerts us to the blind-spots in our thinking and shows how thought itself can be used to ward them off, making possible productive deliberation, and, ultimately, a thinking community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aStupidity. 0aSuperstition. 0aThought and thinking. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  acritical thinking, thought, vices of the mind, superstition, spite, stupidity, generosity, rationality, dissensus, corporate hogwash.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226815572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226815572/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles